{{Proposed deletion/dated |concern = Per [[WP:WEBCRIT]], this needs more than "a brief summary of the nature of the content". Only secondary sources are stories about a startup event that briefly mention Chatous in the context of nine other websites. |timestamp = 20130704094148 }} {{Infobox Website |name = Chatous |logo = |screenshot = |caption = |url = [https://www.chatous.com/ Chatous.com] |alexa = 243,234 ({{as of|2013|7|3|alt=July 2013}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web|url= http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/chatous.com |title= Chatous.com Site Info | publisher= [[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate= 2013-07-03 }}</ref><!--Updated monthly by OKBot.--> |commercial = |type = [[Online chat]], [[voice chat]], [[Videotelephony|video chat]] |language = all |registration = |owner = |authors = Kevin Guo, Dmitriy Karpman, Parth Bhakta |launch date = October 29, 2012 |revenue = |slogan = Chat with real people! }} '''Chatous''' is a [[social discovery platform]] that matches users based on [[Natural Language Processing]] and [[Big Data]] analytics for optimal conversations. The site uses a data-driven approach and algorithm to predict which users will be compatible for conversation, and learns about users as they engage in more conversations. Founded by a team of [[Stanford University]] students, Chatous grew out of a project in a graduate computer science class at Stanford.<ref> {{cite web | last = Ziv | first = Stav | title = Ten New StartX Companies Make Their Public Debut | publisher = [[The Dish Daily]] | date = May 31, 2013 | url = http://www.thedishdaily.com/news/2013/05/31/ten-new-startx-companies-make-their-public-debut}}</ref> Chatous was also part of the [[StartX]] Spring 2013 class, and presented at Demo Day.<ref> {{cite web | last = Taylor | first = Colleen | title =StartX, The Stanford-Affiliated Startup Accelerator, Kicks Off Spring 2013 Demo Day With 10 Company Debuts | publisher = [[Techcrunch]] | date = May 30, 2013 | url = http://techcrunch.com/2013/05/30/startx-the-stanford-affiliated-startup-accelerator-kicks-off-spring-2013-demo-day-with-10-company-debuts/}}</ref> The company has raised an undisclosed amount of seed funding from venture capitalists.<ref> {{cite web | title =Crunchbase| publisher = [[Crunchbase]] | date = June 9, 2013 | url = http://crunchbase.com/company/chatous/}}</ref>
